Curator's comments: The Museum register identifies the item as the "very fine haematite" mentioned by W.M.F. Petrie, Tanis ii, Nebesheh and Defenneh, p. 79 § 78, though the material does not look like hematite.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1888 / Tanis. Part II. Nebesheh (Am) and Defenneh (Tahpanhes) (p. 79 § 78)
Leclère and Spencer 2014 / Tell Dafana Reconsidered: The Archaeology of an Egyptian Frontier Town (p.88, p.188, pl.30)
